!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

appointment /əˈpɔɪntmənt/

(appointments) 

1. N-VAR The appointment of a person to a particular job is the choice of that person to do it. 任命 

例： His appointment to the cabinet would please the right wing. 他进入内阁的任命会令右翼高兴。 

2. N-COUNT An appointment is a job or position of responsibility. 职务; 职位 

例： Mr. Fay is to take up an appointment as a researcher. 费伊先生将担任研究员的职务。 

3. N-COUNT If you have an appointment with someone, you have arranged to see them at a particular time, usually in connection with their work or for a serious purpose. 约会 

例： She has an appointment with her accountant. 她和她的会计师有个约会。 

4. PHRASE If something can be done by appointment , people can arrange in advance to do it at a particular time. 通过预约 

例： Viewing is by appointment only. 参观须预约。

</div>

